            <qtimetadatafield>
              <fieldlabel>grading_notes</fieldlabel>
              <fieldentry>Because it is a machine that operates in a cycle, the state of the machine must always restart once a full cycle is complete. Because energy is a function of state, and the state at the start and end of a cycle are the same, there can be no change in energy. Or, the student could say that it is operating at steady-state which means that the energy that comes in is balanced by what goes out.</fieldentry>
            </qtimetadatafield>
          </qtimetadata>
        </itemmetadata>
        <presentation>
          <material>
            <mattext texttype="text/html">&lt;p&gt;One of the steps to completing this problem is to recognize that the total rate of input energy must equal to the total rate at which energy leaves the machine. Why? Which Law of Thermodynamics requires this?&lt;/p&gt;</mattext>
          </material>
          <response_str ident="response1" rcardinality="Single" rce="Yes" word_count="Yes" spell_check="Yes" word_limit_max="200" word_limit_enabled="Yes">
